# Environment Configuration

This file contains environment variables for the Playwright framework.

## Configuration

```env
# Base URL for the application
BASE_URL=https://opensource-demo.orangehrmlive.com

# CI/CD Flag - set to true in CI pipelines
CI=false

# Test Timeout (in milliseconds)
TEST_TIMEOUT=30000

# Navigation Timeout (in milliseconds)
NAVIGATION_TIMEOUT=30000

# Headless Mode - set to false to see browser
HEADLESS=true

# Video Recording - on, off, or retain-on-failure
VIDEO=retain-on-failure

# Screenshots - on-first-retry, only-on-failure, or off
SCREENSHOTS=only-on-failure

# Parallel Workers - number of workers for parallel execution
WORKERS=4

# Retry Attempts - number of times to retry failed tests
RETRIES=2

# Log Level - DEBUG, INFO, WARN, ERROR
LOG_LEVEL=INFO
```

## Usage

1. Copy this file: `cp .env.example .env`
2. Edit `.env` with your configuration
3. The framework will load these automatically via `dotenv`

## Local Development

For local development:
```env
BASE_URL=https://opensource-demo.orangehrmlive.com
HEADLESS=false
WORKERS=2
RETRIES=0
```

## CI/CD Environment

For CI pipelines:
```env
BASE_URL=https://opensource-demo.orangehrmlive.com
CI=true
HEADLESS=true
WORKERS=1
RETRIES=2
VIDEO=on
```

## Staging Environment

For staging testing:
```env
BASE_URL=https://opensource-demo.orangehrmlive.com
HEADLESS=true
WORKERS=4
RETRIES=1
```

## Production Environment

For smoke testing production:
```env
BASE_URL=https://opensource-demo.orangehrmlive.com
HEADLESS=true
WORKERS=1
RETRIES=3
```

**Note**: Never commit `.env` file to version control. Use `.env.example` as template.
